description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a motivated Dietitian to join our department.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post is 37.5 hours per week and is ideal for the newly qualified Dietitian or a Dietitian with some experience looking to broaden their knowledge and skills. It is a rotational post, offering the opportunity to work in a variety of acute and community services including Amersham, Stoke Mandeville and Wycombe Hospitals. The rotations involve working in gastroenterology, surgery, stroke rehab, respiratory, orthopaedic and community areas.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The acute and community nutrition and dietetic teams are integrated and provide a trust-wide service, consisting of over 40 members of staff based at 4 locations across Buckinghamshire.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We actively encourage CPD and clinical supervision for the professional development of the team. The department has good secretarial / IT support and takes students for B and C placements. Accommodation on site may be available.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Candidates wishing to work part time hours will be considered.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Helen Daly, Head of Nutrition and Dietetics, helen.daly5@nhs.net or Bernadette Tavner Allsopp, Stoke Mandeville Team Lead on [01296] 315775 / email: Bernadette.allsopp@buckshealthcare.nhs.uk.&lt;/p&gt;
